solutions.content:
The idea of this solution is similar with other explanataions, but uses different data structures. The logic contains 2 steps:
1. find all the islands
2. check every cells with zero if they are "bridges" between islands.

In order to use a cell's address as a map key, the solution uses a hash function from the procedure getAddressHash();

The solution uses the next data structures:
* **islands**. It is a list of sets, where a set contains all the cells of the island. So, a size of an island is a size of a set.
* **addressIslandIndex**. It is a map, where a key is the hash of a cell's address and a value is an index of an island that contains this cell. It's used for getting an island index by a cell's address.

So, the algorith of the solution is the next:
1. Go through the matrix and recursively find all the islands.
2. Go through the matrix one more time and if a cell contains 0, check if it is a **bridge** between two islands and can connect them. It's possible to do this by just checking if the neighbouring cells are keys of the structure **addressIslandIndex**. If so, get a size of an island by its index and increase a local max size.

```

class Solution {
    List<Set<Integer>> islands; //Contains all the islands, where an island is a set of all included cells
    Map<Integer,Integer> addressIslandIndex; //Key - a cell, value - index of an island that contains this cell.
    int[][] grid;
    int maxSquare; // result
    public int largestIsland(int[][] grid) {
        //initialise all the variables
        islands = new ArrayList();        
        addressIslandIndex = new HashMap();
        maxSquare=0;
        this.grid = grid;

        //fill list of islands
        for (int i=0;i<grid.length;i++){
            for (int j=0;j<grid.length;j++){
                if (addressIslandIndex.containsKey(getAddressHash(i,j))) continue;
                if (grid[i][j]==1){
                    Set<Integer> island = new HashSet();
                    fillIsland(island, i,j, islands.size());
                    islands.add(island);
                    maxSquare = Math.max(maxSquare,island.size());
                }
            }
        }

        //arrays are used for getting addresses of neighbouring cells
        int[] horizontalOffset = {0,0,1,-1};
        int[] verticalOffset = {1,-1,0,0};

        //System.out.println(islands.size());

        //check all the possible bridges
        for (int i=0;i<grid.length;i++){
            for (int j=0;j<grid.length;j++){                
                if (grid[i][j]==0){
                    int localMax=1;

                    //A set of visited islands is used in order not to use a size of an island several times
                    Set<Integer> visitedIslands = new HashSet();
                    for (int k=0;k<horizontalOffset.length;k++){

                        int addressHash = getAddressHash(i+horizontalOffset[k],j+verticalOffset[k]);
                        if (addressIslandIndex.containsKey(addressHash)){                            
                            int islandIndex = addressIslandIndex.get(addressHash);
                            if (!visitedIslands.contains(islandIndex)){
                                localMax+=islands.get(islandIndex).size();
                                visitedIslands.add(islandIndex);
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    maxSquare = Math.max(maxSquare,localMax);
                }
            }
        }

        return maxSquare;
    }

    private void fillIsland(Set<Integer> island, int i, int j, int islandIndex){
        if (addressIslandIndex.containsKey(getAddressHash(i,j))) return; //cell was already checked
        if (i<0 || j<0 || i>=grid.length || j>=grid.length) return; //cell is out of a grid
        if (grid[i][j]==1){
            island.add(getAddressHash(i,j));            
            addressIslandIndex.put(getAddressHash(i,j),islandIndex);
            //up
            fillIsland(island, i, j-1, islandIndex);
            //down
            fillIsland(island, i, j+1, islandIndex);
            //right
            fillIsland(island, i+1, j, islandIndex);
            //left
            fillIsland(island, i-1, j, islandIndex);
        }
    }

    private int getAddressHash(int i, int j){
        return i*1000 + j;
    }
}

```

