solutions.content:
The main idea of this solution is to update the adjacent `0`s to an island with the size of the island. That way if two neighbouring islands share the same set of `0`s, those cells (with the common `0`s) should be able to tell the maximum size of island (by combining the neighbour islands) if the `0` was turned to `1`. Refer the following:

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/12893b7b-60bd-4dca-99c8-0948d758348c_1644318239.5530734.png)

What we can do to achieve this is:
1. traverse the grid and find a `1` cell. Start BFS from there while keeping track of the size of the island & record any neighbouring adjacent `0` cell encountered while visiting all the cells of one island. 
2. Once we have the size of the island, update the cells having `0` adjacent to the island with the calculated size.
3. Find the maximum value recorded so far.
4. Add 1 to the maximum value recorded (since the cell is `0` and has to be converted to `1` which will add to the size), and return it as answer.

Note: If the entire grid is an island then steps 2 to 4 won't be happening as there won't be any adjacent `0` cell. In this case its easy to identify if the entire grid has been visited already by checking if the size of the island is equal to `n*n`. If so, return that value as answer.


```
class Solution {
    class Pair{
        int x,y;
        public Pair(int x,int y){
            this.x= x;
            this.y=y;
        }
    }

    public int largestIsland(int[][] grid) {
        int n = grid.length;
        int[][]mem = new int[n][n];

        Set<Pair> visited = new HashSet<>();
        int[][]dirs = new int[][]{
                {-1,0}, {1,0}, {0,-1}, {0,1}
        };

        int overallMaxSize = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if(grid[i][j]==1 && !visited.contains(new Pair(i,j))){

                    Set<Pair>zeros = new HashSet<>();

                    ArrayDeque<Pair> dq = new ArrayDeque<>();
                    dq.add(new Pair(i,j));
                    visited.add(new Pair(i,j));
                    int size = 1;
                    while(!dq.isEmpty()){

                        Pair cur = dq.removeFirst();
                        for(int[]dir:dirs){
                            int x = cur.x + dir[0], y = cur.y + dir[1];
                            if(0<=x && x<n && 0<=y && y<n){
                                if(grid[x][y] == 0){
                                    zeros.add(new Pair(x,y));
                                }
                                else if(!visited.contains(new Pair(x,y))){
                                    Pair coords = new Pair(x,y);
                                    dq.add(coords);
                                    visited.add(coords);
                                    size++;
                                }   
                            }
                        }
                    }

                    if(size == n*n) // the entire grid represents an island, nothing can be bigger than this.
                        return size;


                    for(Pair coords:zeros){
                        mem[coords.x][coords.y]+=size;
                        overallMaxSize = Math.max(overallMaxSize, mem[coords.x][coords.y]);
                    }

                }
            }
        }
        return overallMaxSize+1;
    }
}
