![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/bd61d453-bd8e-4294-bb91-999a6921a337_1638398944.285398.png)

3. Create a char array(swapS) of size s.length where we will do the swapping.
4. For each set in the swappable indices set: 
	a. Create a char array  with with a char in s corresponding to each index in the current    set of indices we are in
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/8383fb7f-703e-44b9-a949-c2def221af49_1638398974.2066007.png)

	b. After all char are in inserted in the array then sort the array
	![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/9f30374f-3620-483f-8704-0abee7f86894_1638399034.007516.png)

	c. Now place each char in newS corresponding to each index.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/545d6be7-aff0-4c48-b859-59dbf0672bdd_1638399316.737393.png)

	4. Return swapS char array transformed into a string.
