Idea:

we can group the indexes which are associated via pairs together with `union-find`. The indexes with same id are in the same group. When constructing the result string from the first index, we pick the first letter in lexicographical order in the corresponding index group.

The union-find methods are classic and powerful. I strongly recommend to master union-find algorithm. Here are some good Union-Find problems to enhance your understanding:
[number-of-islands](https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-islands/description/)
[regions-cut-by-slashes](https://leetcode.com/problems/regions-cut-by-slashes/description/)
[surrounded-regions](https://leetcode.com/problems/surrounded-regions/description/)


```
class Solution {
    private int[] ids;  // ids[i] = the id of the string index i. The string indexes with same id are in the same group.
    private Map<Integer, int[]> idToGroup; // key: id, value: letters with frequency
    public String smallestStringWithSwaps(String s, List<List<Integer>> pairs) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

        this.ids = new int[s.length()];
        this.idToGroup = new HashMap<>();

		// initialization
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            this.ids[i] = i;
        }

        for (List<Integer> p : pairs) {
            union(p.get(0), p.get(1));
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            int iId = find(i);
            if (!this.idToGroup.containsKey(iId)) {
                this.idToGroup.put(iId, new int[26]);
            }
            this.idToGroup.get(iId)[s.charAt(i) - 'a']++;  // get the letter frequency
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            int iId = find(i);
            int[] group = this.idToGroup.get(iId);
            for (int j = 0; j < group.length; j++) {
                if (group[j] > 0) { // pick the first letter in lexicographical order
                    sb.append((char)('a' + j));
                    group[j]--; // update the frequency since the letter has been used and cannot be reused anymore
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }

	// classic find method
